## Wrapper client

Keep generated code isolated behind your own service:

```java
@Component
public class PingUserClient {

    private final PartnersBEAP74737ResourceTypeApi pingApi;
    private final PingUserMapper mapper;

    public PingUserClient(
            PartnersBEAP74737ResourceTypeApi pingApi,
            PingUserMapper mapper
    ) {
        this.pingApi = pingApi;
        this.mapper = mapper;
    }

    public String createUser(UserEntity user) {
        PartnersBEAP74737 request = mapper.toCreateRequest(user);

        PartnersBEAP74737 response =
                pingApi.partnersBEAP74737Post(request);

        if (response == null || response.getId() == null) {
            throw new PingIntegrationException(
                    "Ping created the user but returned no resource id"
            );
        }

        return response.getId();
    }
}
```

The generated method and return type may differ. Use the names generated in your API class.

