## Store the Ping resource ID

The create response should return a Ping/SCIM resource ID. Store that ID in Partner Repository, for example:

```text
users.ping_resource_id
```

Then update/delete calls can use:

```text
/scim/v2/partners-BE-AP74737/{pingResourceId}
```

Do not assume your local `userId` or `gpsGroupNumber` is automatically the Ping SCIM `{id}` unless Ping explicitly confirms that.

Suggested columns:

```text
ping_resource_id
ping_sync_status
ping_last_synced_at
ping_last_error
```

